{{Map|3261,3927|r=23|mtype=square|caption=Chaos Elemental's location.|width=250|height=250|align=right}}
Fighting the [[Chaos Elemental]] is a matter of countering its unequip attack by keeping your inventory full and avoiding [[Player killing|player killers]]. As it attacks with random damage types, you will always be taking damage unless you are [[flinching]]. Therefore, it is critical to maximize the amount of healing you bring while minimizing your risk. [[Dragonhide]] armour is effective. '''Always check your [[Items Kept on Death]] before fighting this boss, and never bring anything you are not willing to lose.'''

==Getting there==
* From [[Edgeville]] bank, run south and pull the lever. Bring a [[knife]] or slash weapon to cut the [[web]], then run east past the [[Resource Area]] and [[Scorpion Pit]] (avoid running through it).
* From [[Mage Arena]] bank, pull the lever and cut the two webs. Continue running east.
* After using [[Annakarl Teleport]] or [[Annakarl teleport (tablet)]], run north-west along the fence until you see the gate. Pass through it and run north-east. Requires completion of [[Desert Treasure]].
* If you have completed the hard [[Wilderness Diary]], you can teleport to the [[Wilderness Obelisk]] (Level 50) to get there quickly from the level 13 obelisk near the [[Ferox Enclave]]. This is generally the best option, as it does not require any items and is the shortest.

==Countering the Unequip Attack==
One of the three attacks the elemental may use will unequip up to four of your currently equipped items back to your inventory, prioritizing your weapon. This attack leaves you vulnerable to future attacks, costs time when reequipping, and can distract you from looking out for PKers. Rangers may be dragged into melee range when their weapon is unequipped. '''By keeping your inventory full, this attack will not have any effect.'''

Bring consumables that leave an item behind and have high healing, such as [[Summer pie|summer pies]] (2 &times; 11 hitpoints, 2 &times; 10% run energy), [[curry]] (19 hitpoints), and [[Guthix rest]] (4 &times; 5 hitpoints, 4 &times; 5% run energy). Potions like [[Saradomin brew|Saradomin brews]] will leave a vial behind unless you have talked to the [[Barbarian guard]] and enabled automatic vial smashing (you can use [[NPC Contact]] to disable this).

If such consumables are unavailable, it is also viable to bring one or two sacks of [[potatoes]], [[cabbages]], or [[onions]] to fill your inventory dynamically. Each time you create an empty space by eating food, immediately empty/remove-one vegetable from the sack to fill the empty space. Fill the sack when picking up loot, then empty it again before reengaging. Finally, you can also eat the raw vegetables in a pinch, as they each heal 1 hitpoint.

It may be helpful to remember that the Chaos Elemental will always drop at least two items when killed, often three or more. Be wary of storing items in the [[Looting bag]], as they cannot be removed and may leave you with empty spaces.

==Solo==
[[File:Chaos Elemental safespot.png|thumb|The dead trees at the south-west tip of Rogues' Castle can be used to flinch.]]
The safest method for soloing it would be taking advantage of the hit-and-hide tactic (also referred to as [[flinching]] or hit-and-run) with the usage of nearby trees. This can be done by attracting the Chaos Elemental's attention, and then immediately running behind a tree so it can't attack you. Wait for its [[Hitpoint]] bar to disappear, hit it once, and run back behind the tree. Repeat until the elemental is dead. This method can be done with any [[Melee weapon]]. A full set of [[Verac's equipment]] is recommended for fast kills, but you '''WILL''' [[Items Kept on Death|risk]] the [[Verac's helm]] if you get [[smited]] by a [[PK]] team.

If not using the hit-and-hide tactic, using a [[Karil's leathertop]], [[Verac's helm]] and [[Verac's plateskirt|plateskirt]] with a [[Crystal shield]] or [[Dragonfire shield]] and a [[Rune crossbow]] or [[Armadyl crossbow]] with [[Ruby bolts (e)]] makes this boss very easy to kill, even at sub-100 [[Combat level]]s, but beware of the risk. As there's a strong chance to encounter [[player killers]], it would be better to stick to lower-cost gear to alleviate the risk.

==Team==
Players fighting with [[Melee]] should take armour with high [[Ranged]] and Melee [[Defence]], such as [[Dragon equipment|Dragon]] or [[Barrows equipment]], and use [[Protect from Magic]]. As there's a strong chance to encounter [[player killers]], it would be better to stick to lower-cost gear to alleviate the risk.

