==Avoiding and escaping player killers==
Due to the Chaos Elemental's location in [[Multicombat area|multi-combat]] deep [[Wilderness]], you will likely encounter [[player killers]] in both teams and as individuals. The nearby [[Rogues' Castle]] is useful for attackers to hop worlds (sometimes using low-level scouts) and spot potential victims, as the projectiles are visible beyond normal viewing range. It may be effective to [[World switching|switch worlds]] between kills to potentially avoid PKers and skip the respawn time.

If you are spotted and/or attacked, quickly select and pursue an escape option:

* A [[Wilderness Obelisk]] (Level 50) lies on the south-east side of the [[Rogues' Castle]]. By default the obelisks' destination is random, but it is likely you will be teleported to relative safety such as single-way combat or a lower wilderness level. Completing the hard [[Wilderness Diary]] allows you to select a destination (the level 13 obelisk being the safest, as it is close to the [[Ferox Enclave]]). '''Warning: You cannot use obelisks while under the effect of [[Tele Block]].'''
* The [[Rogues' Castle]] has many doorways and staircases that can be used to confuse and shake loose of an attacker. Moving unpredictably and closing doors behind you can buy you time to log out. This is less effective when being chased by a team.
* The [[Resource Area]] to the west requires {{Coins|7500}} to enter, or less depending on completion of the [[Wilderness Diary]] ({{Coins|6000}} for medium, {{Coins|3750}} for hard, or {{Coins|0}} for elite). If your attacker(s) did not bring coins or lacks the elite diary perk, you can escape them here.
* The [[Magic axe hut]] to the north-west requires a [[Lockpick]] to enter and {{SCP|Thieving|23}} to enter. Although there are aggressive [[Magic axe|magic axes]] contained within which prevent you from logging out, it is in single-way combat. It is very likely that either you or your attacker will be attacked by an axe, which may allow you to [[Logout_button#X-logging|X-log]]. There are also two entrances/exits, which can help you create space.
* The [[Deserted_Keep#Teleport_lever|Deserted Keep]] to the west has a teleport lever which can take you to [[Ardougne]] (or [[Edgeville]], if the easy [[Wilderness Diary]] is completed). A [[web]] blocks the entrance, so bring a [[knife]] or slash weapon to open it. '''Warning: You cannot use the lever while under the effect of [[Tele Block]].'''

If it isn't likely that you will survive, prioritize keeping your [[prayer points]] so that you can keep [[Protect Item]] active. If you run out of prayer restoration, it may be advisable to accept your fate rather than continue eating food, as taking damage allows your attackers to potentially [[smite]] you for your fourth valuable item. Consider bringing a [[Falador shield]] for a last-resort prayer restoration option, as it is free to reobtain. The [[Demonic Ruins]] to the south also passively restore 1 prayer point every 3 seconds, which may provide a slim chance of reactivating Protect Item.

